======================================================================
LOG: Feature Extraction Module & Inspection Pipeline Update
======================================================================
Date: 2026-06-27

----------------------------------------------------------------------
1. NEW FILE: backend/services/feature_extraction.py
----------------------------------------------------------------------
- Created FeatureExtractor class with 5 extraction capabilities:
  a) Defect type classification: Maps YOLO class_name to specific defect
     types (scratch, crack, dent, hole, etc.) based on product class
     and polygon aspect ratio (elongated -> scratch/crack, compact -> dent/hole)
  b) Area calculation: Uses Shoelace formula on polygon coordinates,
     returns pixel area, normalized area, and percentage of image coverage
  c) Position analysis: Divides image into 9 zones (3x3 grid),
     computes centroid of mask/bbox, classifies zone with human-readable description
  d) Size classification: 6 levels (micro, tiny, small, medium, large, critical)
     based on percentage of image area
  e) Severity scoring: 0-100 score combining:
     - Area contribution (0-40): exponential curve favoring larger areas
     - Position contribution (0-30): center zones weighted higher
     - Confidence contribution (0-30): higher conf = higher score
     Result: Low (<25), Medium (25-50), High (50-75), Critical (>75)
     with actionable recommendations per level

- PRODUCT_DEFECT_MAP: 16 product classes with their possible defect types
  (based on MVTec AD common defects)

- POSITION_ZONES: 9-zone grid for spatial defect localization

----------------------------------------------------------------------
2. NEW FILE: backend/services/inspection_report.py
----------------------------------------------------------------------
- Created InspectionReportService class that generates structured inspection reports
- generate_report() produces:
  - inspection_summary: filename, image_size, total_defects, defect_type_breakdown,
    severity_breakdown
  - position_analysis: defect_zones heatmap, most_affected_zone
  - verdict: PASS/FLAG/REJECT with reason
  - recommendations: actionable QC steps based on verdict
  - defect_details: full enriched predictions array
- generate_text_summary(): human-readable text version for VQA context
- Rule-based logic for verdict:
  - Any High/Critical -> REJECT
  - No defects -> PASS
  - >2 Medium -> REJECT
  - 1-2 Medium -> FLAG (secondary inspection)
  - All Low -> PASS

----------------------------------------------------------------------
3. MODIFIED: backend/services/vqa_service.py
----------------------------------------------------------------------
- Added inspection_context parameter to answer_question()
- Added _answer_with_context(): context-aware answering using enriched
  predictions and inspection report. Supports questions about:
  - Defect existence, count, types
  - Severity levels
  - Position/location
  - Verdict (pass/fail)
  - Recommendations
  - Full report summary
- Falls back to Transformers VQA pipeline, then legacy keyword matching
- Legacy _keyword_fallback() preserved for backward compatibility

----------------------------------------------------------------------
4. MODIFIED: backend/main.py
----------------------------------------------------------------------
- Added imports: FeatureExtractor, InspectionReportService
- Added new endpoint POST /inspect:
  Full inspection pipeline following the target flow:
  a) Upload image -> YOLO segmentation (best.pt)
  b) Feature Extraction -> enriched predictions
  c) Save annotated result image
  d) Generate Inspection Report (rule-based verdict)
  e) Pre-compute VQA quick answers for common questions
  f) Return Final Response with all data

  Response includes:
  - enriched predictions with defect_type, area, position, size, severity
  - full inspection report with verdict & recommendations
  - VQA quick answers (defect, severity, verdict, position, count)

